<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-04-01T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-04-01T15:00:00-05:00" n="722" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d722">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.51/897: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bliss</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-01T15:00:00-05:00">April 1, 1933—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>18. Your 29, March 31, 5 p.m. Department desires to obtain your views as
                            to whether there is any possibility that the amount of British held
                            pesos thus released would exceed the amount of the loan.</p>
                        <p>Last sentence, first paragraph. Why would American interests be placed at
                            a disadvantage by this loan?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>